cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper presents a deep learning-based system for automatic wheat disease diagnosis using image analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of weakly supervised deep learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques for crop disease diagnosis, which could also fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of a new dataset for wheat disease, which could fall under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the collection and organization of data. Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks for classification, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
